HEADWORD: Stoical
<hw>Sto"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>stoicus</ets>, Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>sto⟦ium⟧que</ets>. See <er>Stoic</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the Stoics; resembling the Stoics
or their doctrines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not affected by passion; manifesting indifference to
pleasure or pain; especially, bearing pain, suffering, or bad fortune
without complaint.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Sto"ic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Sto"ic*al*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stoichiological</ent>⟦br⟧
